# 🌀 Local TURN Server Full Configuration Guide (Ubuntu 20.04)

This guide provides a complete, end-to-end setup for configuring a **local-only TURN server** using **Coturn** with **Asterisk** and **PJSIP**, ideal for **WebRTC** and **SIP NAT traversal** in a private LAN environment (no public IP or domain required).

---

## 📋 Overview

| Component | Details |
|------------|----------|
| **OS** | Ubuntu 20.04 |
| **TURN Software** | [Coturn](https://github.com/coturn/coturn) |
| **Use Case** | Internal-only TURN relay (no external IP) |
| **Local IP** | `172.25.65.81` |
| **Integrated Systems** | Asterisk + PJSIP |
| **Protocol Ports** | 3478 (UDP/TCP), 5349 (TLS) |

---

## ⚙️ 1. Coturn Installation

Update system and install Coturn:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install coturn -y
